ean, Virginia|McLean, VA]]\n| \n| Vocal & Jazz Dance, \"[[I Love Paris]]\"\n| 1st runner-up\n| Preliminary Swimsuit Award<br><br>Preliminary Talent Award\n|\n|-\n|[[Miss America 1963|1962]]\n| Ann Verner\n| [[Arlington, Virginia|Arlington, VA]]\n| 19 \n| Vocal & Guitar, \"Country Boy\"\n|\n| \n| \n|-\n|[[Miss America 1962|1961]]\n| Scarlett Shinault\n| [[Silver Spring, Maryland|Silver Spring, MD]]\n| 20\n| Vocal, \"[[I Cain't Say No]]\"\n| \n| Non-finalist Talent Award\n| \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n|[[Miss America 1961|1960]]\n| Ruth Rea\n| [[Chevy Chase, Maryland|Chevy Chase, MD]]\n| 18\n| Vocal, \"A Little Brains, A Little Talent\" from ''[[Damn Yankees]]''\n| 3rd runner-up\n| Preliminary Swimsuit Award\n| \n|-\n|[[Miss America 1960|1959]]\n| Virginia Pailes\n| [[Hyattsville, Maryland|Hyattsville, MD]]\n| 21\n| Vocal, \"[[It All Depends on You]]\"\n|\n| Preliminary Talent Award (tie)\n| \n|-\n|[[Miss America 1959|1958]]\n| Lee Berkow\n| [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| 21\n| Vocal, \"Come Rain or Come Shine\"\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n|[[Miss America 1958|1957]]\n| June Cook\n| [[Arlington, Virginia|Arlington, VA]]\n| 20\n| Piano, ''[[Rhapsody in Blue]]''\n| \n| \n| \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n|[[Miss America 1957|1956]]\n| Margo Lucey\n| [[Colesville, Maryland|Colesville, MD]]\n| 20\n| Dramatic Monologue & Vocal, \"[[Autumn Leaves (1945 song)|Autumn Leaves]]\"\n| 1st runner-up\n| \n| Later Mrs. Maryland 1980<br>4th runner-up at Mrs. America 1981 pageant{{cn|date=June 2018}}\n|-\n|[[Miss America 1956|1955]]\n| Judith Dunkle\n|\n| 19\n| Vocal \n| \n| \n| \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFACD;\"\n|[[Miss America 1955|1954]]\n| Linda Weisbrod\n| \n| 21\n| Classical Vocal, \"O Mio Fernando\" from ''[[La favorite]]''\n| Top 10\n| Preliminary Talent Award\n| \n|-\n|[[Miss America 1954|1953]]\n| Helen Smith<ref name=\"wapo130315\">{{cite news |first=John |last=Kelly |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher=[[Graham Holdings Company]] |location=[[Washington, 